---
/**
 * rest-api/0001 · Figure 3 — "the Richardson Maturity Model staircase".
 *
 * Copied VERBATIM from docs/rest-api/lessons/0001-what-makes-an-api-restful.html
 * (figure + svg + figcaption). Lives as an .astro component for the same reason
 * as Fig1/Fig2: raw inline SVG with kebab-case attributes is unreliable inside
 * MDX, but is plain HTML inside .astro.
 *
 * Uses the arw + arwA arrowhead markers (the source defines them once in a shared
 * body-level <svg><defs>); they're embedded here in a local <defs> so the figure
 * renders self-contained (ids + fills unchanged).
 */
---

<figure>
    <svg
        viewBox="0 0 640 270"
        role="img"
        aria-label="Richardson Maturity Model as a staircase: Level 0 plain old XML, Level 1 resources, Level 2 HTTP verbs, Level 3 hypermedia HATEOAS"
    >
        <defs>
            <marker
                id="arw"
                viewBox="0 0 10 10"
                refX="8.5"
                refY="5"
                markerWidth="7"
                markerHeight="7"
                orient="auto-start-reverse"
                ><path d="M0,0 L10,5 L0,10 z" fill="#6b675f"></path></marker
            >
            <marker
                id="arwA"
                viewBox="0 0 10 10"
                refX="8.5"
                refY="5"
                markerWidth="7"
                markerHeight="7"
                orient="auto-start-reverse"
                ><path d="M0,0 L10,5 L0,10 z" fill="#7a1f12"></path></marker
            >
        </defs>
        <g font-family="ui-sans-serif,system-ui,sans-serif">
            <text
                x="320"
                y="18"
                text-anchor="middle"
                font-size="12"
                font-weight="700"
                fill="#111110">THE MATURITY LADDER · CLIMB IT IN 30 SECONDS</text
            >
            <!-- steps -->
            <rect x="14" y="200" width="150" height="46" rx="8" fill="#f7ecea" stroke="#9a2417"
            ></rect>
            <text
                x="89"
                y="220"
                text-anchor="middle"
                font-size="11"
                font-weight="700"
                fill="#9a2417">L0 · Swamp of POX</text
            >
            <text x="89" y="235" text-anchor="middle" font-size="8" fill="#7a2218"
                >one URI, one verb · RPC tunnel</text
            >

            <rect x="174" y="150" width="150" height="46" rx="8" fill="#fbfaf2" stroke="#d8d4c8"
            ></rect>
            <text x="249" y="170" text-anchor="middle" font-size="11" font-weight="700"
                >L1 · Resources</text
            >
            <text x="249" y="185" text-anchor="middle" font-size="8" fill="#6b675f"
                >many URIs (/orders/42)</text
            >

            <rect
                x="334"
                y="100"
                width="150"
                height="46"
                rx="8"
                fill="#eef5ee"
                stroke="#2f5d3a"
                stroke-width="1.6"></rect>
            <text
                x="409"
                y="120"
                text-anchor="middle"
                font-size="11"
                font-weight="700"
                fill="#2f5d3a">L2 · HTTP verbs</text
            >
            <text x="409" y="135" text-anchor="middle" font-size="8" fill="#244a2e"
                >methods + status carry meaning</text
            >

            <rect x="478" y="50" width="150" height="46" rx="8" fill="#eef2f5" stroke="#1f3a5a"
            ></rect>
            <text
                x="553"
                y="70"
                text-anchor="middle"
                font-size="11"
                font-weight="700"
                fill="#1f3a5a">L3 · HATEOAS</text
            >
            <text x="553" y="85" text-anchor="middle" font-size="8" fill="#1f3a5a"
                >responses link next actions</text
            >

            <!-- climbing arrows -->
            <line x1="164" y1="210" x2="186" y2="184" stroke="#6b675f" marker-end="url(#arw)"
            ></line>
            <line x1="324" y1="160" x2="346" y2="134" stroke="#6b675f" marker-end="url(#arw)"
            ></line>
            <line x1="484" y1="110" x2="506" y2="84" stroke="#6b675f" marker-end="url(#arwA)"
            ></line>

            <!-- the pragmatic bar -->
            <line x1="334" y1="92" x2="334" y2="252" stroke="#2f5d3a" stroke-dasharray="3 3"></line>
            <text x="338" y="262" font-size="8.5" fill="#2f5d3a"
                >← most real APIs deliberately stop here</text
            >
        </g>
    </svg>
    <figcaption>
        L0 POX → L1 resources → L2 verbs → L3 hypermedia. The senior move isn't claiming Level 3 —
        it's knowing <strong>Level 2 is the pragmatic industry bar</strong> and saying why your API sits
        where it does on purpose.
    </figcaption>
</figure>
